tp://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
I read a nice post about the issue... basically (and in short version)... EQ was hard, EQ lured in 400k people, some vocal people whined at boards, AC, DAoC, AO weren't hard because vocal people wanted things easier, AC, DAoC, AO didn't get 400k people. Dev's listening to vocal people is good and bad. They should use filters and consideration, like the *used* to in EQ, nowadays it seems that any suggestion that will gimp EQ and make it easier, is approved with devs.<br>
<br>
From a pure business stand point, uber mobs and uber guilds posting uber loots are great marketing tool for company. Making the progress hard and so that accomplishments actually make you feel you did something, keep people logging on and trudging towards higher levels and uberdom.<br>
<br>
I just hate the fact that people yelling wolf are getting EQ gimped down to some simple mindless single-player-game-like (Diablo2 comes to mind) where you don't even need social interaction (remember the &quot;class interdependance&quot; where did it go?). Just simple whackable content. Port stones are 'the suck' as are the 'bind drones'. EQ isn't hard to begin with, it is just hard to people who can't interact with other people.<br>
<br>
Sure, great rewards need more time. But if folks in uber guilds put in 8 hours a day and get results in a week and casual gamer puts in 2 hours a day... he will see the same rewards in few weeks. It is all about networking anyway. For example, NToV was uber place after VP... and only uber guilds did NToV raids. Today, there are pickup raids of casual people clearing NToV (and Ssra mini nameds too). That's great, time passes and rewards come in (levels / AA made it easier too), but voluntary gimping of the game does NOT do any good, it only does harm in long run.<br>
<br>
-myz <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=midgetgod>Midget God</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br>  Posts: 283<br> <font color=#ffffff>(2/9/03 12:46 pm)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: EQ is dying</span><hr size=1> Aye. I agree 100%. Alot of people don't realize when they ask for every wizard to have GSS, ERR, SoS, AT, and SoM they don't realize it would make the game... gimp. When it is that easy then what is the point in playing it? I think EQ however has been good at keeping it all in check for the most part. <p>[63 Sorcerer] <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=69194">Zuratuli</a> (Gnome)</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=jadrax>Jadrax</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Arcanist</span><br>  Posts: 1132<br> <font color=#ffffff>(2/9/03 4:28 pm)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: EQ is dying</span><hr size=1> Game is harder than its ever been right now, it's also more succsessful than its ever been right now. <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=95533"><b>Jadrax Darkfire</b></a><br> 
